=========================
Loading Kaloom ONIE Probe
=========================

Introduction
============

The Kaloom ONIE Probe is a Linux image with...

It is intended to run in-memory...

The ONIE Probe goals:
  - provide a diagnostic image that is:
      - fit to probe the switch configuration
      - extendable (new utilities tools can be added)
  - avoid polluting the switch:
      - run in-memory
      - doesn't alter the disk no partitioning, installation. writing, ...)
      - doesn't alter the boot configuration


Cross-Compiling ONIE Probe
==========================

The Kaloom ONIE Probe is a fork of the main open source ONIE project (GPL).
It is sitting in GitHub under the Kaloom organization. 

To clone the project:
  $ cd ${HOME}
  $ git clone https://github.com/kaloom/onie-probe.git

The project comes with a contribution that creates a Docker image suitable
for cross-compiling ONIE:
  $ cd ${HOME}/onie-probe/contrib/build-env
  $ docker build -t debian:build-env .
  $ docker images | grep build-env
    REPOSITORY      TAG           IMAGE ID        CREATED         SIZE
    debian          build-env     992e9550cc26    3 hours ago     650 MB

To compile the project, start the build container
  $ docker run --privileged --it -v ${HOME}/onie-probe:/home/build/src debian:build-env
  build@<container-id>:~$

then build from the build-config folder:
  $ cd /home/build/src/build-config
  $ make -j4 MACHINEROOT=../machine/kaloom MACHINE=kaloom_onie_probe all demo

Alternatively, you can create a local.make file that will hold the MACHINEROOT and
MACHINE variables and use the simplified command:
  $ make -j4 all demo

When complete, the ONIE binaries are located in build/images:
  $ ls /home/build/src/build/images
    -rw-r--r--. 1 12453128 Feb  6 08:55 demo-diag-installer-x86_64-kaloom_probe-r0.bin
    -rw-r--r--. 1 12453128 Feb  6 08:55 demo-installer-x86_64-kaloom_onie-probe-r0.bin
    -rw-r--r--. 1  8720452 Feb  6 08:51 kaloom_onie-probe-r0.initrd
    -rw-r--r--. 1  3718288 Feb  6 08:55 kaloom_onie-probe-r0.vmlinuz
    -rw-r--r--. 1 31399936 Feb  6 08:56 onie-recovery-x86_64-kaloom_onie-probe-r0.efi64.pxe
    -rw-r--r--. 1 28770304 Feb  6 08:56 onie-recovery-x86_64-kaloom_onie-probe-r0.iso
    -rw-r--r--. 1 12494711 Feb  6 08:55 onie-updater-x86_64-kaloom_onie-probe-r0

where:
    - kaloom_onie_probe-r0.vmlinuz                    is the ONIE kernel image
    - kaloom_onie_probe-r0.initrd                     is the ONIE initramfs (filesystem)
    - onie-recovery-x86_64-kaloom_onie_probe-r0.iso   is the ONIE recovery ISO image (for USB)
    - onie-recovery-x86_64-kaloom_onie_probe-r0.efi64.pxe    ONIE recovery ISO image (PXE variant)
    - onie-updater-x86_64-kaloom_onie_probe-r0        is the ONIE self-update image
    - demo-diag-installer-x86_64-kaloom_onie_probe-r0.bin    the ONIE Probe image 
    - demo-installer-x86_64-kaloom_onie_probe-r0.bin         the ONIE Probe image (same as above)


